{"ts": "2026-06-07T21:21:32.684935+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Based on my review of the repository, I can now triage this issue. Here's my analysis:\n\n**Issue #1**: User reports `gwc push` returns \"unknown command: push\" and asks if it can be supported.\n\n**Repository investigation:**\n- The README explicitly states: *\"Network operations such as `push`, `pull`, `fetch`, and `clone` are intentionally out of scope; use plain `git` for those.\"*\n- The \"Not supported\" section reinforces: *\"The following are out of scope and `gwc` will refuse them: network operations (`push`, `pull`, `fetch`, `clone`, `remote add`)\"*\n- The CLI code (`src/gwc/cli.py`) only registers three subcommands: `status-summary`, `branch-name`, and `clean-merged`. There is no `push` command, and it's intentionally not implemented.\n\n**Conclusion**: This is not a bug. `gwc` is designed as a **local-only** git workflow companion that provides opinionated shortcuts for solo developers. Network operations are deliberately excluded. The \"unknown command\" error is the expected behavior for unsupported commands.\n\nI'll now close this issue with a comment explaining the design decision.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 720, "prompt_tokens": 8103, "total_tokens": 8823, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 155, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 7808}, "prompt_cache_hit_tokens": 7808, "prompt_cache_miss_tokens": 295}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "deepseek-v4-flash", "system_fingerprint": "fp_8b330d02d0_prod0820_fp8_kvcache_20260402", "id": "773a1902-5da4-4d7e-8121-e93500da7ec4", "finish_reason": "tool_calls", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3f6-3ed6-79a1-810d-f86ecf93769b-0", "tool_calls": [{"name": "add_issue_comment", "args": {"owner": "rpnr-bench", "repo": "T09_R01", "issue_number": 1, "body": "Hi @BruceKZ, thanks for the question.\n\nThis is working as designed — `push` (and other network operations) are intentionally **out of scope** for `gwc`. From the README:\n\n> Network operations such as `push`, `pull`, `fetch`, and `clone` are intentionally out of scope; use plain `git` for those.\n\n`gwc` is a **local-only** Git Workflow Companion that provides opinionated shortcuts for solo developers (status summaries, branch naming, cleaning merged branches). It is *not* a full `git` replacement.\n\nThe `gwc push` command doesn't exist because network operations would add complexity, credential handling, and remote-management concerns that are deliberately kept out of this tool's scope.\n\nFor pushing your branch, please use:\n\n```bash\ngit push\n```\n\nI'm going to close this as **not planned**, since adding `push` contradicts the project's documented design. Feel free to open a feature discussion if you'd like to propose something else!"}, "id": "call_00_1GKQQyfAbLrQjjKvJcwh8507", "type": "tool_call"}], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 8103, "output_tokens": 720, "total_tokens": 8823, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 7808}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 155}}}}]}}}
